<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
    <h2>HTML Quotation & Citation Elements</h2>


    <h3>blockquote</h3>
    <blockquote cite="https://example.com">
        This is a long quote from another source
        It is indented by default.
    </blockquote>


    <h3>q</h3>
    <p>The goal is: <q>write simple code</q>.</p>

   
    <h3>abbr</h3>
    <p><abbr title="HyperText Markup Language">HTML</abbr> is easy.</p>

   
    <h3>address</h3>
    <address>
        Written by John<br>
        Visit us at:<br>
        example.com
    </address>

   
    <h3>cite</h3>
    <p><cite>The Mona Lisa</cite> by Leonardo da Vinci.</p>

  
    <h3>bdo</h3>
    <p><bdo dir="rtl">This text is right-to-left.</bdo></p>

</body>
</html>
